WEBVTT

00:07.125 --> 00:09.583
[soft instrumental music plays]

00:23.166 --> 00:25.833
[soft music swells]

00:51.625 --> 00:53.333
[thunder crashes]

00:54.291 --> 00:55.958
[rousing music plays]

01:18.166 --> 01:19.958
[music fades out]

01:20.041 --> 01:24.041
-[phone beeping]
-[soft thunder rumbles]

01:24.625 --> 01:25.833
[man groans]

01:25.916 --> 01:26.791
[gunshot]

01:27.666 --> 01:30.375
[woman] There's a group of men
called The Firm.

01:31.416 --> 01:32.500
[door rattling]

01:32.583 --> 01:35.791
They've been running things
for a long, long time.

01:37.583 --> 01:40.375
And when they need someone
to clean up their mess…

01:40.458 --> 01:43.083
-[insistent banging at door]
-…they send me.

01:43.166 --> 01:45.375
[ominous music]

01:45.458 --> 01:46.791
[banging continues]

01:48.500 --> 01:50.166
[stroke of a gong]

01:51.458 --> 01:53.500
[rousing music plays]

02:18.416 --> 02:19.875
[music fades out]

02:19.958 --> 02:22.125
[woman on TV] Go get your helmet.
Let's go to the store.

02:22.208 --> 02:25.666
-[character squeaks in protest]
-You look so cute, Nit.

02:26.833 --> 02:28.750
[voices argue on TV]

02:28.833 --> 02:30.625
[phone rings]

02:37.791 --> 02:38.916
[Sam sighs]

02:40.916 --> 02:43.416
-[man on speakerphone] Sam.
-Nathan.

02:44.541 --> 02:47.875
-[Nathan] Where are you?
-At home. Sewing.

02:48.916 --> 02:50.375
Meet me at the diner.

02:53.000 --> 02:54.041
Why?

02:55.291 --> 02:56.916
How much trouble am I in?

02:57.000 --> 03:00.291
["You'll Never Know" by Bobby Darin plays]

03:00.375 --> 03:01.666
[service bell dings]

03:01.750 --> 03:04.083
[song continues over diner sound system]

03:04.166 --> 03:06.458
An extra scoop for my favorite client.

03:06.541 --> 03:07.708
Thanks, Rose.

03:11.083 --> 03:13.000
[ominous musical sting]

03:13.083 --> 03:15.666
["Half a Photograph" by Kay Starr
plays in background]

03:18.250 --> 03:21.000
I put in an extra scoop
for my favorite client.

03:21.083 --> 03:24.208
-Thanks, Rose,
-I'm sure she won't be long.

03:25.375 --> 03:27.583
You clearly don't know
my mother very well.

03:32.500 --> 03:35.250
-[thunder rumbles]
-[slow suspenseful music]

03:41.833 --> 03:43.125
Hey, stranger.

03:43.208 --> 03:45.791
-Can I lighten your load?
-Not carrying today, Rose.

03:45.875 --> 03:49.041
There's a first time for everything.
She's over there.

03:49.583 --> 03:51.791
Thanks for keeping an eye on her.

03:51.875 --> 03:54.458
[rousing instrumental music]

04:13.916 --> 04:16.583
-[music fades out]
-You said you'd be here in 30 minutes.

04:17.250 --> 04:18.500
I'm a few minutes late.

04:20.000 --> 04:21.333
Three hours.

04:27.958 --> 04:28.833
You're bleeding.

04:28.916 --> 04:30.083
[thunder rumbles]

04:30.166 --> 04:32.791
Just another day at the office.
Did you bring it?

04:34.750 --> 04:35.875
[Sam sighs]

04:42.166 --> 04:43.791
Anna May sure can pick them.

04:44.500 --> 04:46.541
-It's loaded.
-Good girl.

04:52.083 --> 04:54.875
Listen, I, um…
have to disappear for a while.

04:55.708 --> 04:58.833
-Then I'm coming with you.
-You can't. Not this time.

04:59.750 --> 05:02.375
Nathan will be here soon.
He'll take care of you when I'm gone.

05:02.458 --> 05:05.708
-I don't want to go with Nathan.
-I'm doing this for your own good.

05:05.791 --> 05:07.958
I'll stay in the library
with Anna May and the others.

05:08.583 --> 05:09.625
It's too dangerous.

05:13.166 --> 05:14.583
What's going on?

05:14.666 --> 05:16.291
[emotional music]

05:17.000 --> 05:19.125
It's… it's complicated.

05:19.750 --> 05:20.625
Tell me.

05:21.791 --> 05:23.000
I'm not a kid any more.

05:24.458 --> 05:25.500
No, you're not.

05:37.083 --> 05:39.041
You haven't touched your milkshake.

05:39.916 --> 05:42.250
Didn't want to drink it without you.

05:53.000 --> 05:55.375
[climactic music]

06:17.958 --> 06:19.333
[music fades out]

06:19.875 --> 06:21.541
How long will you be gone?

06:25.291 --> 06:27.166
I have to make a quick phone call.

06:28.583 --> 06:29.791
Stay here.

06:40.041 --> 06:43.291
-[door crashes open]
-[suspenseful music]

06:44.000 --> 06:46.583
[Rose] Evening, gentlemen.
Can I lighten your load?

06:46.666 --> 06:48.125
-Get lost.
-Hey.

06:51.791 --> 06:53.791
[suspenseful music plays]

07:10.625 --> 07:12.541
[ominous music plays]

07:19.250 --> 07:21.208
[in Russian accent] Hello, little girl.

07:22.500 --> 07:24.666
Mommy says I'm not allowed
to talk to strangers.

07:26.333 --> 07:30.166
This "Mommy" looks a lot like you.

07:31.708 --> 07:34.416
Only bigger and more stabby.

07:35.875 --> 07:38.333
Got my father's blood all over her.

07:42.833 --> 07:44.666
I don't like you.

07:44.750 --> 07:45.958
[gasps mockingly]

07:53.416 --> 07:54.625
Enough games.

07:55.875 --> 07:57.166
Where is she?

07:58.416 --> 08:00.375
[in Russian] Go kiss a pig.

08:00.458 --> 08:02.083
[music intensifies]

08:03.916 --> 08:08.375
[in English] Tell me where she is.

08:11.041 --> 08:13.708
[suspenseful music intensifies]

08:14.541 --> 08:16.750
-[gun cocks]
-Close your eyes, baby girl.

08:16.833 --> 08:18.583
-[gunshots]
-[glass smashing]

08:20.458 --> 08:23.458
-[gunshots continue]
-[panicked grunts and shouts]

08:23.541 --> 08:26.166
-[man exclaims in Russian]
-[gunshots continue]

08:26.958 --> 08:28.708
[high-pitched ringing]

08:29.333 --> 08:31.583
-[hurried steps]
-[door slams]

08:32.250 --> 08:34.833
["Something on Your Mind"
by Karen Dalton plays]

08:37.791 --> 08:38.625
Mom!

08:47.958 --> 08:50.125
♪ Yesterday ♪

08:51.125 --> 08:56.166
♪ Any way you made it was just fine ♪

08:57.791 --> 09:02.083
♪ So you turn your days into nighttime ♪

09:03.875 --> 09:06.541
♪ Didn't you know ♪

09:07.333 --> 09:12.750
♪ You can't make it
Without ever even trying ♪

09:14.958 --> 09:19.708
♪ And something's on your mind
Isn't it? ♪

09:22.833 --> 09:24.583
♪ Let these times-- ♪

09:24.666 --> 09:28.791
[music crescendos and fades]

09:29.958 --> 09:31.708
[quiet music playing in diner]

09:31.791 --> 09:32.666
Evening, darling.

09:32.750 --> 09:34.833
-Can I lighten your load?
-I'm clean.

09:34.916 --> 09:37.000
Regular clean or diner clean?

09:38.875 --> 09:40.000
[chuckles ironically]

09:40.958 --> 09:42.000
[sighs]

09:44.375 --> 09:46.416
-Forgot about this one.
-Of course, sugar.

09:46.500 --> 09:47.541
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

09:52.958 --> 09:54.666
[distant thunder rumbles]

09:55.666 --> 09:56.958
[Nathan whispers] Boy.

09:57.541 --> 10:00.541
Oh, these girls are worse than the Stasi.

10:01.291 --> 10:02.916
[sighs] You hurt?

10:04.708 --> 10:06.500
Just another day at the office.

10:06.583 --> 10:08.791
Wow, you sound just like your mother.

10:10.291 --> 10:11.708
I don't have a mother.

10:11.791 --> 10:14.375
Well, you sure have her temper.

10:15.625 --> 10:17.208
What the hell happened tonight?

10:17.291 --> 10:19.041
Bad intel.

10:19.125 --> 10:22.000
You said four or five idiots
with peashooters.

10:22.083 --> 10:23.416
Yes. And?

10:23.500 --> 10:25.333
[discordant tone]

10:27.000 --> 10:28.125
[diner bell dings]

10:29.916 --> 10:31.916
Oh, for Christ's sake, child.

10:33.041 --> 10:35.916
This was supposed to be low-profile,
not a bloody massacre.

10:36.000 --> 10:38.125
Next time, I'll just let them shoot me.

10:38.208 --> 10:41.125
Next time, just do what you're told.

10:42.916 --> 10:46.083
Remember who you're working for.
As long as they're happy…

10:46.166 --> 10:49.750
You called me here oh-so-urgently
just to remind me of that?

10:52.000 --> 10:53.000
No.

10:54.125 --> 10:56.208
Your talents are needed, pronto.

10:57.583 --> 10:59.208
Somebody stole from us.

11:01.416 --> 11:03.750
Who's crazy enough to steal from The Firm?

11:04.250 --> 11:06.375
Somebody who doesn't know
who we really are.

11:06.458 --> 11:09.291
An accountant.
From the clean side of the business.

11:10.333 --> 11:11.833
How much did he take?

11:11.916 --> 11:13.791
Enough to earn a visit from you.

11:13.875 --> 11:15.083
We need that money back.

11:16.625 --> 11:18.208
[whispers] Good girl.

11:18.291 --> 11:20.625
I'll text you the address later.

11:20.708 --> 11:24.166
Oh, and get rid of
those stone-age firearms you carry.

11:24.250 --> 11:27.041
-I've had them for years.
-Find an open vendor.

11:27.125 --> 11:29.833
And get yourself some clean boomsticks.

11:29.916 --> 11:32.625
We can't have you linked
to that war zone you left behind, can we?

11:33.541 --> 11:34.666
[thunder rumbles]

11:35.750 --> 11:37.875
[soft suspenseful music plays]

11:47.791 --> 11:51.375
[man] Did you know about this
little endeavor my son had on the side?

11:52.916 --> 11:55.875
[nephew] Sorry, Uncle. I had no idea.

11:57.458 --> 11:58.833
[exasperated sigh]

12:01.500 --> 12:02.958
[grunts, exhales]

12:21.166 --> 12:22.375
Where's the shoe?

12:23.666 --> 12:24.791
What shoe?

12:24.875 --> 12:28.000
The shoe that is not currently covering
my son's left foot.

12:28.708 --> 12:30.791
The one that looks like the right one.

12:30.875 --> 12:32.083
That fucking shoe.

12:32.666 --> 12:34.791
-I don't know.
-Well, find it.

12:42.458 --> 12:44.375
[sidekick] Found it, Mr. McAlester.

13:05.291 --> 13:07.458
Nobody tells his mother about this.

13:09.166 --> 13:11.625
We'll tell her he ran off with some girl.

13:12.333 --> 13:13.291
I get it.

13:14.083 --> 13:17.333
Now, bring me the heads of the men
that killed my boy.

13:17.416 --> 13:19.708
-[music fades out]
-[church bells chiming]

13:24.750 --> 13:26.041
[sighs]

13:33.333 --> 13:35.416
[door slams heavily]

13:37.166 --> 13:39.541
[church bells continue]

13:48.541 --> 13:49.708
[librarian] Hmm.

13:52.041 --> 13:53.250
[quiet chuckle]

13:53.333 --> 13:55.333
[inhales deeply]

13:56.458 --> 13:57.375
[sharp exhale]

13:59.000 --> 14:00.000
Hello, dear.

14:00.500 --> 14:01.791
What can I do for you?

14:04.541 --> 14:07.041
I need to exchange some… books.

14:08.000 --> 14:09.250
Well, that's nice.

14:09.916 --> 14:12.625
Not a lot of people your age
read nowadays.

14:13.500 --> 14:15.416
-Do you have a card with us?
-No.

14:16.083 --> 14:17.166
I'd like to open one.

14:17.916 --> 14:19.375
Wonderful.

14:19.458 --> 14:21.875
What kind of… books are you interested in?

14:22.958 --> 14:24.208
Mostly smaller ones.

14:25.083 --> 14:25.958
A few heavies.

14:26.708 --> 14:28.375
Well, you won't find them there.

14:28.458 --> 14:30.375
Those are our children's sections.

14:30.458 --> 14:31.583
The Enchanted Forest…

14:33.041 --> 14:34.958
and The Never-Ending Ocean.

14:36.875 --> 14:38.208
They sound like fun.

14:39.833 --> 14:41.250
[soft music plays]

14:41.333 --> 14:42.708
Have we met before?

14:44.000 --> 14:46.833
You seem so… familiar.

14:48.291 --> 14:51.791
I'm embarrassed to say it's been a while
since I visited a library.

14:52.625 --> 14:55.541
[quietly]
Well, that's no way to live, dear.

14:57.166 --> 14:58.916
Let's get you into a good book.

14:59.833 --> 15:00.666
Come.

15:05.250 --> 15:06.583
[keys jangle]

15:07.875 --> 15:09.416
[suspenseful music]

15:12.125 --> 15:13.541
[key turns in lock]

15:17.375 --> 15:18.708
[door creaks]

15:26.875 --> 15:29.958
[music plays quietly in background]

15:32.083 --> 15:36.416
Anna May, this lovely young lady
wants to open an account with us.

15:40.125 --> 15:41.333
Well,

15:42.125 --> 15:45.416
Madeleine should have told you
that we don't accept new readers

15:45.500 --> 15:46.875
without a reference.

15:47.416 --> 15:49.291
Madeleine had a hunch.

15:49.375 --> 15:52.541
Fudge your hunches,
if you pardon my French.

15:52.625 --> 15:55.375
-Technically not French.
-Always literal.

15:55.458 --> 15:58.791
-Yes, I'm literary. I'm a librarian.
-Be that as it may.

15:58.875 --> 16:00.791
-Florence, dear.
-[music stops]

16:00.875 --> 16:02.208
Would you join us?

16:02.291 --> 16:04.000
[footsteps approach]

16:04.791 --> 16:06.875
I'm afraid we need a tie-breaker.

16:07.625 --> 16:10.750
Madeleine thinks this girl
needs to do some reading.

16:10.833 --> 16:12.375
I told you I had a hunch.

16:12.458 --> 16:14.291
There's something very familiar about her.

16:14.375 --> 16:15.708
Hunch, smunch.

16:15.791 --> 16:19.208
I, on the other hand,
think we should dispose of the body

16:19.291 --> 16:22.875
and then have a long talk
about our onboarding protocols.

16:22.958 --> 16:24.500
You know I can hear you, right?

16:26.208 --> 16:27.625
Hush, girl.

16:28.166 --> 16:29.375
Don't be rude.

16:30.750 --> 16:32.041
Turn around, hon.

16:32.583 --> 16:33.708
[annoyed sigh]

16:42.000 --> 16:43.416
And take off your hat.

16:52.625 --> 16:54.500
What did you say your name was?

16:54.583 --> 16:55.666
She didn't.

16:55.750 --> 16:57.375
[Florence] Hmm. That's odd.

16:57.916 --> 16:59.333
[Anna May] Well, girl?

17:00.291 --> 17:02.625
Cat got your tongue? Speak up.

17:04.458 --> 17:05.666
It's Sam.

17:05.750 --> 17:07.500
[soft dramatic music]

17:07.583 --> 17:09.291
Scarlet's kid.

17:10.000 --> 17:11.083
[Sam] Yeah.

17:11.583 --> 17:14.000
I knew it. Never forget those eyes.

17:14.083 --> 17:16.958
We haven't seen you
since you were yea high.

17:17.041 --> 17:18.416
How is your mother?

17:19.041 --> 17:21.250
[Sam] Haven't seen her in 15 years.

17:21.333 --> 17:22.291
[Anna May sighs]

17:23.541 --> 17:27.000
Well, that's something
we both have in common.

17:27.791 --> 17:30.541
[Madeleine] My, my, my. Little Sam.

17:31.125 --> 17:33.708
We hear about you all the time.

17:33.791 --> 17:36.666
You've made
quite a reputation for yourself.

17:36.750 --> 17:39.166
Come here. Give Auntie Madeleine a hug.

17:43.375 --> 17:44.750
Why come back now?

17:46.916 --> 17:48.041
I needed clean guns…

17:50.125 --> 17:52.041
and I guess I needed an excuse.

17:52.833 --> 17:54.083
[music stops]

17:55.541 --> 17:56.666
[impressed whistle]

17:56.750 --> 17:58.583
Nice collection.

17:59.333 --> 18:01.333
And you take good care of them.

18:01.416 --> 18:04.583
Let me guess. You're the sentimental type.

18:05.125 --> 18:07.125
Ro-man-tique.

18:07.208 --> 18:09.750
Sentimental types
don't last long doing this.

18:09.833 --> 18:13.708
So, no. I don't think
I'm the sentimental type.

18:13.791 --> 18:15.291
Tommy Tomahawk.

18:15.791 --> 18:17.666
I looked everywhere for him.

18:17.750 --> 18:19.541
Yeah, sorry about that.

18:20.666 --> 18:21.625
So…

18:23.166 --> 18:24.875
you're an idealist.

18:24.958 --> 18:27.583
Nope. Maybe I don't have a type.

18:27.666 --> 18:29.416
Everybody has a type.

18:29.500 --> 18:31.000
-Everybody.
-Mm-hmm.

18:31.083 --> 18:33.375
Maybe I'm the professional type?

18:33.458 --> 18:35.541
Ah. Old school.

18:36.125 --> 18:37.875
"No women, no children" type.

18:39.875 --> 18:41.208
Women are fair game.

18:41.875 --> 18:42.958
Gender equality.

18:43.583 --> 18:45.000
Very progressive.

18:45.083 --> 18:46.500
She's a feminist.

18:47.708 --> 18:49.000
Fine.

18:49.083 --> 18:50.791
You get to live.

18:50.875 --> 18:52.416
We'll make these disappear

18:52.500 --> 18:55.916
and get you into some new, clean books.

18:56.000 --> 18:57.208
[rousing music]

18:57.291 --> 18:58.666
You'll need a Jane Austen.

18:59.458 --> 19:00.291
[thuds]

19:01.125 --> 19:02.333
A Charlotte Brontë.

19:03.833 --> 19:05.833
And a Virginia Woolf.

19:09.208 --> 19:11.458
[Madeleine] Oh, and an Agatha Christie.

19:15.958 --> 19:17.625
-For reading.
-[phone rings]

19:19.041 --> 19:20.375
[dramatic music]

19:26.166 --> 19:28.708
[up-tempo instrumental music]

19:50.916 --> 19:52.541
[music fades out]

19:59.875 --> 20:01.166
[door creaks quietly]

20:06.208 --> 20:08.958
-[cookware clinking]
-[footsteps]

20:09.750 --> 20:12.750
[water running]

20:25.625 --> 20:27.666
[cheerful ringtone plays]

20:28.958 --> 20:30.541
[suspenseful music]

20:32.958 --> 20:34.291
[ringtone continues]

20:36.666 --> 20:37.708
Please.

20:38.916 --> 20:41.541
-[cheerful ringtone plays]
-I need to answer this.

20:41.625 --> 20:46.375
[Sam] You need to walk away
and thank God I'm not in a killing mood.

20:46.458 --> 20:48.166
[cheerful ringtone plays]

20:48.875 --> 20:50.250
I got no choice.

20:55.041 --> 20:56.833
-[man] No!
-[Sam] Enough!

20:57.541 --> 20:58.958
[gunshot]

20:59.041 --> 21:00.250
[Sam gasps]

21:02.375 --> 21:04.583
-[cheerful ringtone plays]
-[grunting]

21:07.250 --> 21:08.250
[exhales sharply]

21:09.875 --> 21:11.750
[pained grunting]

21:15.041 --> 21:16.875
[cheerful ringtone plays]

21:25.125 --> 21:26.833
[ominous music]

21:27.541 --> 21:29.541
[man on speaker] Playing hard to get?

21:29.625 --> 21:31.666
Not very smart, moron.

21:32.208 --> 21:36.166
Not unless you want me to send
your little princess back in pieces.

21:36.666 --> 21:38.375
You have exactly 60 minutes

21:38.458 --> 21:41.208
to bring the money
to the Gutterball bowling alley.

21:41.291 --> 21:43.625
A minute late, and she'll be celebrating

21:43.708 --> 21:45.666
her ninth birthday with the worms.

21:46.166 --> 21:47.833
60 minutes.

21:51.541 --> 21:52.708
Please.

21:53.416 --> 21:54.708
[man] It's my daughter.

21:59.416 --> 22:01.875
[distorted]
♪ Yesterday ♪

22:03.625 --> 22:06.125
♪ Any way you made it was just fine ♪

22:07.333 --> 22:08.500
[dramatic musical sting]

22:09.750 --> 22:11.000
Fuck me.

22:11.083 --> 22:13.625
[tense music]

22:25.083 --> 22:26.208
[man grunting in pain]

22:29.916 --> 22:31.250
[gust of wind blows]

22:36.583 --> 22:38.583
[emotional music plays]

22:44.500 --> 22:46.041
[elevator dings]

22:46.125 --> 22:47.666
[music fades out]

22:50.833 --> 22:52.791
["Try to Remember" by Matt Monro plays]

22:52.875 --> 22:55.458
♪ Try to remember ♪

22:55.541 --> 22:59.000
♪ The kind of September ♪

23:01.958 --> 23:03.625
[nurse] I'll get the doctor.

23:04.291 --> 23:06.125
Guns go in the cookie jar.

23:10.125 --> 23:11.916
-[ominous music]
-[man grunts]

23:13.791 --> 23:16.416
-Hey. Haven't seen you in a while.
-Hmm.

23:17.416 --> 23:19.125
And you brought a new friend.

23:19.625 --> 23:21.583
-What the hell happened?
-I happened.

23:21.666 --> 23:22.916
Just fix him.

23:23.000 --> 23:25.125
I need him on his feet in ten minutes.

23:29.208 --> 23:31.375
-[man moans]
-[doctor] Ooh.

23:31.458 --> 23:32.958
He's not going anywhere.

23:33.041 --> 23:34.333
Not in ten minutes.

23:35.250 --> 23:36.166
Maybe not ever.

23:36.250 --> 23:38.291
-So what can we do?
-"We"?

23:39.166 --> 23:41.125
Well, you can start
by not shooting people.

23:41.208 --> 23:43.625
[man whispers] Please. My Emily.

23:43.708 --> 23:45.333
-There's no time.
-[doctor] Shh.

23:45.458 --> 23:47.625
Just relax. Take it in deep.

23:47.708 --> 23:49.250
Is that laughing gas?

23:49.875 --> 23:50.708
Well, duh.

23:51.750 --> 23:52.750
Just patch him up.

23:53.250 --> 23:54.500
I'll be back soon.

23:55.291 --> 23:56.625
He'd better be functional.

24:02.750 --> 24:04.541
She's quite annoying, isn't she?

24:04.625 --> 24:06.833
[rousing music plays]

24:06.916 --> 24:09.166
[laughs] Who am I talking to?

24:09.250 --> 24:11.250
The guy that she shot in the stomach?

24:11.333 --> 24:13.833
-[music intensifies]
-[inhales deeply]

24:13.916 --> 24:16.375
-[tires screech]
-[motor revving]

24:16.458 --> 24:17.625
[car horn honking]

24:17.708 --> 24:20.083
-[Nathan] Is it done?
-There's a change of plan.

24:20.916 --> 24:23.166
What are you talking about?
What does that mean?

24:23.250 --> 24:26.333
They kidnapped his little girl.
That's why he stole the money.

24:26.416 --> 24:29.291
If I'm not at the Gutterball
in 15 minutes, they'll kill her.

24:29.375 --> 24:32.833
Sam, you're not thinking straight.
Just bring the money back, now!

24:32.916 --> 24:36.000
I just need half an hour.
I'll release her and bring the money.

24:37.375 --> 24:39.750
Okay. Listen to me, Sam.

24:40.500 --> 24:43.625
If you screw this one up,
they will give the kill order.

24:44.458 --> 24:46.750
And I won't be able to stop them.

24:47.250 --> 24:49.208
She's just a little girl.

24:49.291 --> 24:50.916
I can't leave her to die.

24:52.291 --> 24:54.625
-I'm sorry.
-Don't you dare hang up on me.

24:54.708 --> 24:55.958
-I'm sorry.
-Don't you--

24:56.041 --> 24:57.083
Fuck.

24:57.791 --> 24:58.875
[sighs]

25:02.916 --> 25:04.166
[exhales deeply]

25:06.458 --> 25:07.625
[clears throat]

25:09.916 --> 25:11.666
[soft dramatic music]

25:12.333 --> 25:15.250
Go to the Gutterball.
Try to reason with her.

25:16.375 --> 25:17.416
Bring back the money.

25:19.083 --> 25:20.208
Wait.

25:23.583 --> 25:25.416
Now, when I say "reason with her,"

25:25.500 --> 25:28.041
I mean no guns, no knives.

25:28.125 --> 25:29.708
She comes back alive.

25:29.791 --> 25:32.208
-Understood?
-[together] Yeah.

25:34.166 --> 25:35.208
And for God's sake…

25:37.000 --> 25:37.833
be careful.

25:38.541 --> 25:40.166
Remember who you're dealing with.

25:43.708 --> 25:45.166
What are you waiting for? Go.

25:45.833 --> 25:47.708
[tense music plays]

26:01.750 --> 26:04.375
[whispers] One of the men Sam killed
was Jim McAlester's son.

26:07.833 --> 26:10.333
[low] Are you sure
it was McAlester's kid?

26:10.416 --> 26:11.708
[whispers] Yes.

26:13.500 --> 26:15.666
The board is on its way.

26:24.791 --> 26:26.500
Goddammit, Sam.

26:41.375 --> 26:43.125
[soft eerie music]

26:54.666 --> 26:56.416
[cheerful ringtone plays]

27:01.875 --> 27:04.375
[man] Who the fuck are you?

27:05.375 --> 27:08.000
[Sam] Just someone who has your money.

27:08.625 --> 27:09.833
I want the girl.

27:09.916 --> 27:11.208
[man] Where's Daddy?

27:12.291 --> 27:13.416
He…

27:14.083 --> 27:15.083
had an accident.

27:16.291 --> 27:17.333
He sent me.

27:19.875 --> 27:21.541
Do you want your money or not?

27:28.666 --> 27:30.791
[ominous music]

27:38.291 --> 27:39.833
[cheerful ringtone plays]

27:42.791 --> 27:45.416
[man]
The girl got to this point alive.

27:45.500 --> 27:47.041
But if you as much as sneeze

27:47.125 --> 27:48.583
without my permission,

27:48.666 --> 27:51.250
that could be easily rectified.

27:52.000 --> 27:54.083
-Got it.
-Good.

27:54.166 --> 27:56.625
Now, see the locker behind you?

27:57.833 --> 27:59.125
[electronic buzzing]

28:00.583 --> 28:02.916
Weapon and phone go in the locker,

28:03.000 --> 28:04.875
along with the clothes you're wearing.

28:04.958 --> 28:07.208
Slam the door shut, and it'll lock.

28:07.291 --> 28:10.208
Go to the Westfield Mall
across the street.

28:10.291 --> 28:12.708
You, the suitcase, the new clothes

28:12.791 --> 28:14.666
and the little girl's phone.

28:16.916 --> 28:18.416
Seriously?

28:19.000 --> 28:20.708
Ten minutes.

28:26.916 --> 28:29.041
[dramatic music intensifies]

28:40.166 --> 28:41.125
Hello, Sam.

28:41.208 --> 28:43.375
-[Sam sighs]
-[cheerful whistling plays]

28:43.458 --> 28:44.583
[Sam] Bonehead.

28:45.166 --> 28:47.083
-Hey, Sam.
-Sam.

28:47.166 --> 28:48.375
[Sam laughs]

28:49.791 --> 28:51.041
Boneheads.

28:53.791 --> 28:57.416
-I really don't have time for this.
-Nathan's worried about you.

28:58.000 --> 29:00.916
Doesn't want you to do anything stupid.

29:01.000 --> 29:03.500
So why don't you hand over the suitcase,

29:04.208 --> 29:05.291
and nobody gets hurt.

29:05.375 --> 29:10.208
Counter-offer: Go back to Nathan,
tell him you tried, but I roughed you up.

29:10.291 --> 29:11.750
[inhales sharply] Ooh.

29:12.250 --> 29:14.916
You can beat each other up
for added realism.

29:16.125 --> 29:17.750
-That's funny.
-[Sam] What?

29:17.833 --> 29:19.791
No guns today?

29:19.875 --> 29:21.791
Nathan doesn't want you hurt.

29:23.083 --> 29:24.666
Not too badly, anyway.

29:24.750 --> 29:26.958
Oh, that is so sweet.

29:28.583 --> 29:30.625
I'll try not to kill you, too.

29:32.916 --> 29:36.750
[rousing rock music plays]

29:37.750 --> 29:41.083
[whistling mariachi music plays]

29:43.416 --> 29:45.500
[neck cracking]

29:49.291 --> 29:50.958
[electrical buzzing]

29:55.500 --> 29:58.166
-[mariachi music continues]
-♪ We can fight ♪

29:58.916 --> 30:00.541
♪ Fight, fight ♪

30:01.083 --> 30:02.958
♪ Fight, fight, fight ♪

30:07.125 --> 30:08.833
-[yelling]
-[blows]

30:14.500 --> 30:15.833
[grunting]

30:23.291 --> 30:25.333
[Dracula] Who the fuck is she?

30:26.291 --> 30:27.541
♪ We can fight ♪

30:27.625 --> 30:29.250
[music intensifies]

30:29.333 --> 30:31.416
[grunting and yelling continues]

30:41.958 --> 30:43.625
-[metallic blow]
-[shouting]

30:43.708 --> 30:44.708
[laughs]

30:49.750 --> 30:51.541
[man screams]

31:03.166 --> 31:04.625
[music softens]

31:14.416 --> 31:15.916
[musical intensifies]

31:16.458 --> 31:18.458
-[blows]
-[grunting]

31:18.541 --> 31:19.791
[taser buzzes]

31:25.500 --> 31:27.666
-[bones crack]
-[thug screams]

31:41.916 --> 31:43.708
-[loud crack]
-[man screams]

31:45.291 --> 31:46.791
♪ We can fight ♪

31:52.583 --> 31:54.500
[intense music continues]

31:58.583 --> 32:00.708
-[music stops]
-[high-pitched ringing]

32:03.916 --> 32:06.083
[music resumes]
♪ We can fight ♪

32:13.916 --> 32:15.333
[music fades out]

32:16.333 --> 32:18.000
[Sam panting]

32:19.416 --> 32:21.041
[cheerful ringtone plays]

32:21.833 --> 32:23.250
[breathes heavily]

32:24.000 --> 32:26.458
[Dracula] Ground floor. Video Beast.

32:31.333 --> 32:32.666
[echoing silence]

32:52.708 --> 32:54.208
[door creaking]

32:54.833 --> 32:56.083
[door slams shut]

33:06.166 --> 33:07.625
[suspenseful music]

33:09.208 --> 33:10.541
Cutting it close.

33:11.291 --> 33:12.583
I had a few hiccups.

33:12.666 --> 33:16.416
We saw what you did with those hiccups.
How do we know you're not a cop?

33:17.083 --> 33:19.000
Can a cop do what I just did?

33:20.166 --> 33:21.291
I just want the girl.

33:22.708 --> 33:24.833
Then we'll get along just fine.

33:24.916 --> 33:26.750
There's a shopping cart behind you.

33:28.166 --> 33:29.833
Put the suitcase inside.

33:37.500 --> 33:39.750
[Dracula]
Push the shopping cart towards us,

33:39.833 --> 33:42.208
and we'll push the girl cart towards you.

33:44.000 --> 33:45.041
One.

33:45.125 --> 33:47.375
[suspenseful music]

33:47.458 --> 33:48.791
[Dracula] Two.

33:51.083 --> 33:52.458
Three.

33:53.916 --> 33:56.875
[soft, dreamy music]

33:59.583 --> 34:01.208
-[suspenseful music]
-[men cackling]

34:02.583 --> 34:03.916
It's okay. You're safe.

34:04.000 --> 34:05.875
-[Emily whimpers]
-I'll be right back.

34:05.958 --> 34:07.791
-[fast-paced music]
-[Emily screams]

34:12.208 --> 34:15.666
[Dracula] We're all stinking rich,
you magnificent bastards.

34:16.208 --> 34:17.916
[Frankenstein] Stop the fucking car.

34:18.416 --> 34:19.708
[Wolfman] Holy fuck!

34:21.583 --> 34:23.458
-[tires screech]
-[smashing]

34:23.541 --> 34:25.041
[explosion]

34:25.125 --> 34:27.916
-[distant screaming]
-[glass smashing]

34:32.875 --> 34:34.333
[cheerful music]

34:35.166 --> 34:36.791
[screams]

34:39.666 --> 34:41.041
[gunshots]

34:42.333 --> 34:44.583
[Dracula] You greedy traitor!

34:45.250 --> 34:46.458
[screams, grunts]

34:46.541 --> 34:47.916
[rapid gunfire]

34:53.458 --> 34:54.541
[gun clicks]

35:01.583 --> 35:03.333
[music fades out]

35:03.416 --> 35:05.125
No… no!

35:05.208 --> 35:06.250
No, no, no!

35:07.958 --> 35:09.458
[screaming]

35:14.333 --> 35:15.500
[sighs]

35:18.500 --> 35:19.458
[whispers] Fuck.

35:22.708 --> 35:24.166
[paper rustles]

35:30.333 --> 35:32.833
-[gunshot]
-[dramatic music resumes]

35:32.916 --> 35:34.625
[gun clicking]

35:39.291 --> 35:40.375
[gun clicks]

35:45.000 --> 35:46.416
[strangled scream]

35:57.500 --> 35:58.833
[music fades]

35:59.333 --> 36:00.541
Anything broken?

36:00.625 --> 36:02.250
-Are you bleeding?
-No.

36:02.333 --> 36:04.000
Bleeding on the inside?

36:04.708 --> 36:05.875
How can you tell?

36:06.541 --> 36:07.708
It's inside.

36:08.791 --> 36:10.833
You're probably fine. Let's go.

36:11.708 --> 36:13.000
Try to keep up.

36:15.166 --> 36:18.166
-[slow cheerful music]
-[thugs giggling]

36:22.458 --> 36:23.875
[thugs snorting]

36:25.541 --> 36:28.666
I see you morons have found my stash.

36:28.750 --> 36:30.750
[thug] This is some good shit, doc.

36:30.833 --> 36:32.958
You should be very proud of yourself.

36:35.000 --> 36:37.125
This is not a toy.

36:37.208 --> 36:39.250
It's for medicinal use only.

36:40.416 --> 36:41.791
[quiet giggling]

36:47.708 --> 36:48.791
So…

36:49.791 --> 36:51.625
who fucked you up like this?

36:51.708 --> 36:53.583
[inhales sharply, snorts]

36:56.000 --> 36:58.250
-A girl.
-[thugs laugh hysterically]

36:59.166 --> 37:02.416
A girl made you look
like you're from The Walking Dead?

37:02.500 --> 37:04.583
I've never felt
pain like this before, doc.

37:05.458 --> 37:07.416
[leader] She got us good, doc. I…

37:08.583 --> 37:10.208
I don't think I'll ever walk again.

37:11.750 --> 37:13.250
There must be an epidemic,

37:13.333 --> 37:16.291
'cause I got a guy in the next room
who's got similar symptoms.

37:17.250 --> 37:18.291
What do you mean?

37:18.375 --> 37:19.583
I mean…

37:20.500 --> 37:23.083
a girl fucked him up, too.

37:24.666 --> 37:26.250
[cheerful music plays]

37:27.916 --> 37:29.791
Keep talking, doc.

37:30.583 --> 37:32.666
-[Sam sighs]
-You're bleeding.

37:34.083 --> 37:35.416
It's just a scratch.

37:35.500 --> 37:37.166
It can get infected.

37:38.083 --> 37:42.166
Worms will get in there and lay eggs.
Then they'll have to cut your arm off.

37:44.583 --> 37:46.541
That's what they teach in school
these days?

37:47.125 --> 37:48.083
Discovery Channel.

37:48.875 --> 37:51.166
Thank God we're going straight
to the hospital.

37:51.791 --> 37:52.791
Is my daddy there?

37:52.875 --> 37:54.625
[emotional music]

37:55.125 --> 37:56.208
Yeah.

37:57.041 --> 37:58.875
Is that why he didn't come?

37:59.625 --> 38:00.708
Is he sick?

38:01.708 --> 38:02.666
He…

38:03.916 --> 38:05.083
[Emily] It's okay.

38:05.166 --> 38:07.166
You don't have to lie for him.

38:08.041 --> 38:10.250
He never comes when he says he will.

38:17.583 --> 38:20.458
Here, just let me help you.

38:20.541 --> 38:21.708
[seatbelt clicks]

38:24.708 --> 38:25.666
Thank you.

38:28.708 --> 38:29.541
Sure.

38:31.833 --> 38:33.166
Are you sure it's her?

38:33.250 --> 38:35.625
[leader] Yeah. She dropped off
some guy she shot.

38:35.708 --> 38:38.375
Said she's going to come back
and pick him up later.

38:38.458 --> 38:40.208
-[thugs laugh]
-And the money?

38:40.875 --> 38:43.375
-She had it last time we saw her.
-[laughing]

38:43.958 --> 38:45.375
Then get it back.

38:45.458 --> 38:48.333
She's still getting the VIP treatment?

38:49.500 --> 38:50.708
[ominous music]

38:57.541 --> 39:00.458
-Do whatever it takes.
-Alright, alright, alright.

39:00.541 --> 39:03.250
Now that's what I call a work benefit.

39:04.791 --> 39:05.875
[elevator dings]

39:17.416 --> 39:19.541
[Sam] Just, uh, stay behind me, okay?

39:21.958 --> 39:23.500
[ominous music]

39:40.958 --> 39:42.083
Come on.

39:49.083 --> 39:50.125
[gasps]

39:59.375 --> 40:01.666
[slow delicate music]

40:18.375 --> 40:19.958
[emotional music]

40:27.958 --> 40:29.125
[sobs]

40:35.875 --> 40:37.125
I'll get the doctor.

40:51.166 --> 40:52.250
She's here.

40:53.750 --> 40:54.916
Shot in the shoulder.

41:00.541 --> 41:02.625
Maybe you should take your break now.

41:10.291 --> 41:12.125
So. My payment?

41:13.125 --> 41:15.583
-Oh! [sharp inhale]
-Shh.

41:15.666 --> 41:17.333
Transferred to your account.

41:18.375 --> 41:19.333
Now…

41:19.833 --> 41:21.458
What's the plan, doc?

41:21.541 --> 41:22.916
[hysterical laughter]

41:24.625 --> 41:25.791
[together] Oh.

41:25.875 --> 41:29.166
Once I stick her with this,
she'll start losing control of her arms.

41:29.250 --> 41:30.750
[snickering]

41:30.833 --> 41:32.666
After 60 seconds or so…

41:33.875 --> 41:35.083
she's a sitting duck.

41:35.166 --> 41:37.875
[suspenseful music]

41:46.000 --> 41:48.500
-[door opens]
-[music intensifies]

41:55.000 --> 41:57.250
What's wrong with you?
Let me do this right.

41:57.333 --> 41:59.166
It's just a scratch.

41:59.250 --> 42:00.791
Well, scratches get infected.

42:00.875 --> 42:02.375
That's how you lose an arm.

42:03.125 --> 42:05.625
Mm. Yeah, I heard.

42:08.166 --> 42:09.541
[liquid sloshes]

42:10.500 --> 42:11.583
What happened to him?

42:12.916 --> 42:14.125
Someone shot him.

42:14.208 --> 42:16.333
I hear that's pretty lethal.

42:17.875 --> 42:19.458
Let's fix this.

42:19.541 --> 42:21.458
Don't. I'm good.

42:22.250 --> 42:24.125
Trust me, you'll need this.

42:25.083 --> 42:27.125
[loudly] I said, I'm good.

42:30.166 --> 42:31.458
I'm sorry, I didn't mean--

42:31.541 --> 42:32.958
[medical gun clicks twice]

42:35.458 --> 42:37.916
-You motherfu--
-[music crescendos]

42:38.625 --> 42:40.916
-[Sam] Ah!
-60 seconds!

42:42.125 --> 42:43.833
[doctor shouts] 60 seconds!

42:45.958 --> 42:47.416
[breathes heavily]

42:50.916 --> 42:52.666
[whispers] 60 seconds.

42:53.916 --> 42:56.166
[through gritted teeth]
Oh, come on. Come on!

42:56.833 --> 42:58.041
[breathes heavily]

43:00.083 --> 43:02.208
Listen, I need your help.

43:03.083 --> 43:05.250
Some bad men are coming to hurt us.

43:05.916 --> 43:07.333
Those who killed my dad?

43:07.416 --> 43:10.375
I promise I'll explain,
but right now I need your help, okay?

43:10.458 --> 43:11.875
-Okay.
-Good.

43:11.958 --> 43:13.416
Grab the biggest knife.

43:14.333 --> 43:15.791
Careful of the sharp end.

43:15.875 --> 43:17.250
[metallic clink]

43:19.125 --> 43:20.375
[whispers] Okay…

43:20.458 --> 43:21.416
Now grab the tape.

43:25.375 --> 43:27.208
Excellent. Tape it to my hand.

43:31.291 --> 43:32.916
[whispers] 36…

43:33.000 --> 43:35.250
[suspenseful music]

43:35.333 --> 43:36.708
[whispers] 32…

43:45.708 --> 43:47.666
Now tape the gun to my other hand.

43:49.208 --> 43:50.583
Careful. It's loaded.

43:51.333 --> 43:53.541
[whispers] 15… 14…

43:54.500 --> 43:56.333
[intense dramatic music]

43:57.250 --> 43:58.833
Round two, bitch.

43:59.500 --> 44:01.125
[thugs snickering outside]

44:01.208 --> 44:02.291
Boneheads?

44:02.375 --> 44:05.291
-Better get ready!
-[snickering]

44:05.375 --> 44:07.833
Oh, thank God it's just you three.

44:07.916 --> 44:10.750
For a second there,
I thought it was someone dangerous.

44:11.625 --> 44:15.125
The only reason you're still alive
is 'cause Nathan wanted it that way.

44:16.458 --> 44:19.333
[quietly] Now, take my finger
and put it on the trigger.

44:19.416 --> 44:21.166
[leader] Well, it's over now.

44:21.708 --> 44:24.125
I'm going to tear you into little pieces.

44:24.625 --> 44:27.666
And I'm gonna love every second of it.

44:27.750 --> 44:29.000
Great. Hold that thought.

44:29.625 --> 44:31.166
[Sam] I'll be right out.

44:33.416 --> 44:34.583
[leader chuckling]

44:35.291 --> 44:37.333
[rousing music]

44:41.750 --> 44:43.583
You're being very brave, Emily.

44:44.166 --> 44:46.416
I need you to do one last thing for me,

44:46.500 --> 44:48.458
and then go and hide, okay?

44:49.875 --> 44:50.916
Okay.

44:58.208 --> 45:00.125
[intense music escalates]

45:06.333 --> 45:07.916
[cheerful mariachi music plays]

45:08.000 --> 45:09.750
[men grunting]

45:09.833 --> 45:11.166
[Sam grunts]

45:19.208 --> 45:21.000
-[mariachi music continues]
-[cackles]

45:26.416 --> 45:27.916
[grunts]

45:38.583 --> 45:40.166
[screaming]

45:41.916 --> 45:43.000
[gunshots]

45:52.750 --> 45:53.750
[Sam gasps]

45:56.250 --> 45:57.750
[gunshots continue]

46:00.458 --> 46:01.666
[both growling]

46:03.583 --> 46:04.875
[grunts with exertion]

46:05.750 --> 46:07.666
-[Sam yells]
-[flesh tearing]

46:10.625 --> 46:12.291
-[Sam grunting]
-[leader screams]

46:15.541 --> 46:16.583
[roar]

46:16.666 --> 46:18.291
[mariachi music continues]

46:20.541 --> 46:21.750
[grunts]

46:24.666 --> 46:27.458
[man screams and whimpers]

46:31.500 --> 46:33.208
[Sam grunts]

46:37.958 --> 46:39.375
[screams]

46:41.583 --> 46:42.916
[flesh tearing]

46:45.708 --> 46:46.875
-[vigorous roar]
-[Sam grunts]

46:54.458 --> 46:55.750
[leader shouts]

47:00.166 --> 47:02.375
[shotgun clicking]

47:02.458 --> 47:04.125
[mariachi music intensifies]

47:05.000 --> 47:06.083
[Sam grunts]

47:13.708 --> 47:15.291
[shotgun clicks]

47:15.375 --> 47:17.125
Hey, Bonehead.

47:21.000 --> 47:22.416
[laughs]

47:23.708 --> 47:25.708
-[resonant crash]
-[music stops abruptly]

47:25.791 --> 47:28.041
-[Sam pants]
-[phone rings]

47:31.208 --> 47:32.250
[grunts]

47:33.333 --> 47:34.458
[groans]

47:37.000 --> 47:38.875
[phone rings]

47:38.958 --> 47:40.666
[panting continues]

47:48.666 --> 47:50.166
[phone rings]

47:53.458 --> 47:54.458
Emily.

47:57.416 --> 47:59.708
I need you to come grab the phone.

48:03.625 --> 48:06.208
[quiet ominous music]

48:09.750 --> 48:11.166
[phone rings]

48:14.416 --> 48:15.833
Come on. [pants]

48:16.875 --> 48:18.500
[phone rings]

48:20.000 --> 48:22.125
It's okay. Just pick it up.

48:26.458 --> 48:27.958
[phone rings]

48:28.916 --> 48:32.083
[breathing heavily]
You are a goddamn rock star.

48:32.166 --> 48:33.500
Put it on speaker.

48:35.750 --> 48:37.750
[Nathan] Someone better start talking.

48:37.833 --> 48:38.833
That was a…

48:40.125 --> 48:43.916
jerk move,
sending the Three Stooges after me.

48:45.041 --> 48:47.500
You left us no choice, Sam.

48:47.583 --> 48:48.875
There's always a choice.

48:48.958 --> 48:51.291
[Nathan] Oh, well, then,
we can still figure this out.

48:51.375 --> 48:53.208
Just bring the money back.

48:53.291 --> 48:56.583
[Sam] It's gone. The suitcase
was blown to 1000 pieces.

48:58.375 --> 48:59.875
[exhales incredulously]

49:00.375 --> 49:01.541
Oh.

49:04.875 --> 49:06.458
That's really unfortunate.

49:07.833 --> 49:09.166
So now what?

49:09.916 --> 49:11.875
[Nathan] Oh, you know the drill, Sam.

49:11.958 --> 49:13.875
You're no longer under our protection.

49:15.666 --> 49:18.416
[Nathan] In your little massacre
earlier tonight,

49:18.500 --> 49:20.500
you killed the wrong people.

49:20.583 --> 49:23.000
Including Jim McAlester's son.

49:24.541 --> 49:25.916
But I was sent by you.

49:26.750 --> 49:27.791
By The Firm.

49:27.875 --> 49:29.291
It doesn't matter.

49:30.333 --> 49:32.166
[tense emotional music plays]

49:32.958 --> 49:34.750
This is business, Sam.

49:35.583 --> 49:38.291
And you landed on the wrong side
of the balance sheet.

49:39.083 --> 49:40.208
So…

49:41.875 --> 49:43.750
It needs to be rectified.

49:46.833 --> 49:48.750
How's this for business?

49:50.125 --> 49:51.833
If I get out of this alive,

49:52.708 --> 49:54.375
I'm coming for you.

49:56.458 --> 49:57.541
All of you.

49:59.416 --> 50:01.083
I would expect no less.

50:03.375 --> 50:04.666
Goodbye, Sam.

50:11.333 --> 50:12.416
[sniffs]

50:18.750 --> 50:20.416
[tense emotional music fades]

50:20.500 --> 50:22.916
[zippers closing]

50:26.375 --> 50:27.833
[phone rings]

50:30.583 --> 50:33.541
-[McAlester] Yes?
-Mr. McAlester, this is Nathan.

50:33.625 --> 50:36.291
I'm the head of the HR department
here at The Firm.

50:36.375 --> 50:37.583
What do you want?

50:37.666 --> 50:40.916
To prevent an all-out war
between our two fine organizations,

50:41.000 --> 50:45.208
we would like to offer you
the woman responsible for your loss.

50:45.291 --> 50:47.541
So you had nothing to do with this?

50:47.625 --> 50:51.000
I can assure you, this is not how The Firm
conducts its business, sir.

50:51.083 --> 50:55.666
It was an unsolicited action
by a very troubled individual.

50:55.750 --> 50:57.958
Now, I'm sending you her last location.

50:58.541 --> 51:01.500
I hope this is satisfactory, sir.

51:02.250 --> 51:03.458
[McAlester] For now.

51:04.791 --> 51:05.958
[phone beeps off]

51:06.041 --> 51:07.625
Take everybody.

51:08.166 --> 51:10.125
Don't come back until it's done.

51:15.791 --> 51:17.541
-[sighs]
-[soft dramatic music]

51:21.208 --> 51:22.375
[clears throat]

51:23.666 --> 51:24.875
[cocks gun]

51:27.000 --> 51:28.416
[phone rings]

51:32.875 --> 51:34.541
[soft dramatic music]

51:36.375 --> 51:39.208
-It's a text message from Nathan.
-What's it say?

51:40.000 --> 51:43.750
"I'm sorry, child.
I can no longer protect you."

51:44.875 --> 51:48.166
"I left you a package to help you
survive the next few days."

51:48.750 --> 51:50.541
"Take it, and disappear."

51:51.958 --> 51:53.375
Then there's an address.

51:54.791 --> 51:56.166
That's close by.

51:57.666 --> 51:59.000
What if it's a trap?

52:00.291 --> 52:01.166
[elevator dings]

52:11.583 --> 52:13.041
[suspenseful music]

52:14.541 --> 52:17.791
Can you press the button?
We're parked on minus two.

52:19.916 --> 52:21.208
[elevator creaks]

52:27.750 --> 52:29.208
[music intensifies]

52:32.291 --> 52:33.583
[music stops abruptly]

52:35.416 --> 52:36.958
[doctor panting]

52:44.541 --> 52:46.875
Just remember, you were spared

52:46.958 --> 52:49.000
thanks to an eight-year-old girl.

52:49.083 --> 52:50.916
[Emily] Eight and three quarters.

52:53.333 --> 52:54.500
Sorry.

52:55.041 --> 52:56.625
Eight and three quarters.

53:00.541 --> 53:01.583
[elevator dings]

53:07.875 --> 53:09.416
Are you a serial killer?

53:10.958 --> 53:11.875
What?

53:13.458 --> 53:16.166
[defensively] No…
Where did you learn that expression?

53:16.791 --> 53:18.750
-History Channel.
-Well…

53:19.666 --> 53:21.625
I am not a serial killer.

53:21.708 --> 53:23.875
But… you kill people?

53:24.458 --> 53:25.833
Yes.

53:25.916 --> 53:27.833
So that makes you a killer.

53:27.916 --> 53:29.875
And you've killed more than one.

53:29.958 --> 53:31.333
That is serial.

53:33.250 --> 53:34.250
It's…

53:34.333 --> 53:36.000
It's more complicated than that.

53:36.833 --> 53:40.375
Serial killers are, uh,
you know, mentally unstable.

53:40.458 --> 53:42.791
They kill people out of a compulsive urge.

53:45.583 --> 53:47.041
So, why do you kill them?

53:49.583 --> 53:51.083
For money?

53:52.416 --> 53:54.041
Again, it's, uh…

53:55.250 --> 53:56.708
It's complicated.

53:58.083 --> 53:59.375
[sighs]

53:59.458 --> 54:02.291
Look, I'm going to need your help
for a little longer.

54:02.375 --> 54:04.000
Because your arms are still paralyzed?

54:04.083 --> 54:06.125
Yes. After that,
I'll get you to your mother.

54:06.208 --> 54:07.708
She left a long time ago.

54:07.791 --> 54:09.916
-To your grandparents, then.
-They're dead.

54:10.000 --> 54:12.250
Uncles? Anything?

54:18.083 --> 54:20.375
[soft music plays]

54:21.875 --> 54:23.916
We'll figure it out, okay?

54:25.583 --> 54:26.583
Okay.

54:27.416 --> 54:30.000
So, here's an unrelated question.

54:31.416 --> 54:32.708
Do you know how to drive?

54:34.125 --> 54:36.250
[Sam] Let's go over it
one more time. Left.

54:37.166 --> 54:38.208
[Sam] Right.

54:38.291 --> 54:39.875
Yes, I've got it already.

54:39.958 --> 54:42.208
"D" is for drive. "R" is for reverse.

54:42.291 --> 54:45.458
And you get to do the easy part,
stepping on the gas and breaks.

54:46.125 --> 54:48.458
Don't be a smart-ass. Turn the key.

54:48.541 --> 54:50.333
[engine revs]

54:50.416 --> 54:51.750
Put it in drive.

54:53.166 --> 54:54.375
Let's go.

54:58.250 --> 55:00.291
[suspenseful music]

55:14.041 --> 55:15.791
That's it. Straighten up.

55:17.750 --> 55:19.041
[laughs] I'm driving.

55:19.625 --> 55:20.708
Yes, you are.

55:20.791 --> 55:22.125
[tires screeching]

55:22.208 --> 55:23.958
[engines revving]

55:25.125 --> 55:26.833
[tires screeching]

55:29.250 --> 55:31.166
-Don't worry about the bullets.
-[guns cocking]

55:32.416 --> 55:33.708
Reverse. Now.

55:35.791 --> 55:38.208
-[engine revs]
-Hard left!

55:40.666 --> 55:42.291
-Put it in drive.
-Yeah.

55:43.166 --> 55:44.458
[tires screeching]

55:44.541 --> 55:45.875
-[Emily panting]
-That's it.

55:47.666 --> 55:49.125
-Hard left.
-[tires screech]

55:49.208 --> 55:50.708
-Go, go, go.
-[smashing]

55:52.583 --> 55:54.083
[rapid gunfire]

55:54.708 --> 55:55.541
[man] Damn it!

55:56.208 --> 55:57.791
[Sam] Get ready. Hard left.

55:59.500 --> 56:00.833
And another hard left.

56:02.625 --> 56:03.708
[tires screech]

56:05.250 --> 56:06.750
-[screeching of tires]
-Shh.

56:12.958 --> 56:14.333
[ominous music]

56:15.500 --> 56:18.041
[whispers] Okay. Put it in reverse.

56:22.208 --> 56:24.583
-Hard right!
-[engine revving]

56:26.250 --> 56:27.625
[Sam] Put it in drive.

56:33.000 --> 56:34.291
Hard left.

56:35.125 --> 56:36.958
Put it in reverse. [panting]

56:38.875 --> 56:41.083
-[tense music plays]
-Okay, kill the lights!

56:48.833 --> 56:51.166
[suspenseful music]

57:03.250 --> 57:05.416
[suspenseful music continues]

57:05.500 --> 57:07.750
[whispers] Okay, be quiet. Duck down.

57:07.833 --> 57:09.708
That's it. Get down.

57:12.125 --> 57:13.125
[horn honks]

57:17.583 --> 57:19.458
[men shouting]

57:21.166 --> 57:24.000
[Sam whispers] Okay. Put it in drive…

57:25.666 --> 57:26.875
and close your eyes.

57:28.291 --> 57:30.166
[rapid gunfire]

57:33.000 --> 57:34.541
[rapid gunfire]

57:37.166 --> 57:38.083
[both grunting]

57:41.000 --> 57:42.333
Keep her straight.

57:44.583 --> 57:46.583
[smashing]

57:47.791 --> 57:48.666
Keep it straight.

57:49.250 --> 57:50.375
[screaming]

57:51.125 --> 57:52.208
[grunts]

57:56.125 --> 57:57.625
Are your eyes still closed?

57:58.250 --> 57:59.541
-Yes.
-Good girl.

58:00.083 --> 58:01.375
Put it in reverse.

58:02.083 --> 58:03.625
[Emily breathes shallowly]

58:04.250 --> 58:05.541
[gasps]

58:07.708 --> 58:09.208
[engine revving]

58:15.666 --> 58:16.583
[grunts]

58:16.666 --> 58:18.791
[car clanks and rattles]

58:18.875 --> 58:20.625
-[engine revs]
-[tires screech]

58:28.083 --> 58:29.833
[Emily] Can I turn on the radio?

58:30.750 --> 58:32.250
Go nuts.

58:34.041 --> 58:35.791
["French Disko" by Stereolab plays]

58:35.875 --> 58:37.791
♪ Though this world's essentially ♪

58:37.875 --> 58:40.916
♪ An absurd place to be living in ♪

58:41.000 --> 58:45.625
♪ It doesn't call for bubble withdrawal ♪

58:47.250 --> 58:50.458
♪ I've been told it's a fact of life ♪

58:50.541 --> 58:51.875
[music fades out]

58:53.250 --> 58:55.000
[song resumes on radio]

58:55.541 --> 58:58.416
♪ Though this world's essentially ♪

58:58.500 --> 59:01.875
♪ An absurd place to be living in ♪

59:01.958 --> 59:05.708
♪ It doesn't call for bubble withdrawal ♪

59:05.791 --> 59:07.125
[phone rings]

59:08.083 --> 59:09.250
[song ends abruptly]

59:24.458 --> 59:25.833
[suspenseful music plays]

59:29.916 --> 59:32.166
[Sam whispering] Emily, doorbell.

59:34.625 --> 59:35.916
[doorbell rings]

59:47.500 --> 59:49.750
[music intensifies]

59:52.541 --> 59:53.625
[music stops abruptly]

59:54.541 --> 59:56.791
[woman] Didn't I teach you
to always guard your back?

1:00:02.750 --> 1:00:03.958
[gasps]

1:00:07.458 --> 1:00:08.833
[tremulously] Hi, Mom.

1:00:10.333 --> 1:00:11.416
[whispers] Hi.

1:00:13.541 --> 1:00:15.250
[soft emotional music]

1:00:21.083 --> 1:00:22.500
[whispers] Is this, um…

1:00:24.958 --> 1:00:25.916
Am I a grandmother?

1:00:27.125 --> 1:00:28.291
God, no.

1:00:29.708 --> 1:00:31.208
[sharp exhale]

1:00:32.000 --> 1:00:34.000
Hi. I'm Emily.

1:00:34.750 --> 1:00:36.958
-I'm her apprentice.
-What?

1:00:37.041 --> 1:00:38.125
Emily.

1:00:38.625 --> 1:00:39.833
Come.

1:00:40.416 --> 1:00:42.041
[sighs, sniffs]

1:00:48.666 --> 1:00:51.583
[on TV] …the additional burden
of needing to care

1:00:51.666 --> 1:00:53.708
for her twelve-month-old daughter.

1:00:53.791 --> 1:00:55.166
It will be at least a year…

1:00:55.875 --> 1:00:57.416
[electrical zapping]

1:01:01.958 --> 1:01:04.333
That is a hell of a story.

1:01:05.833 --> 1:01:07.625
Mm. Hell of a night.

1:01:09.916 --> 1:01:12.375
Um… Try wiggling your fingers.

1:01:13.041 --> 1:01:15.833
-Feeling should come back in no time.
-Yeah, it's already working.

1:01:15.916 --> 1:01:17.291
Excellent.

1:01:21.416 --> 1:01:23.541
You look really good. Are you eating well?

1:01:23.625 --> 1:01:24.791
Cut the crap, Ma.

1:01:26.625 --> 1:01:28.708
Where have you been for the last 15 years?

1:01:30.000 --> 1:01:31.083
Around.

1:01:34.375 --> 1:01:35.500
Watching you.

1:01:38.041 --> 1:01:39.666
Making sure you're safe.

1:01:40.333 --> 1:01:41.625
Great parenting.

1:01:42.250 --> 1:01:44.458
Glad to see you taking an interest
in my career.

1:01:44.541 --> 1:01:47.791
-I never wanted this life for you.
-How's that working out for you?

1:01:52.708 --> 1:01:55.916
I wanted to stay with you
and your aunts, but I couldn't.

1:01:56.666 --> 1:01:57.916
Why not?

1:02:00.875 --> 1:02:02.166
Because I fucked up.

1:02:08.125 --> 1:02:09.458
[quietly] I fucked up.

1:02:11.458 --> 1:02:13.125
I was young when I had you.

1:02:13.208 --> 1:02:14.416
[soft emotional music]

1:02:15.041 --> 1:02:17.666
We left London, followed your father here.
When he died--

1:02:17.750 --> 1:02:19.541
When he was murdered.

1:02:21.916 --> 1:02:24.708
When he was murdered,
you were a baby. I had nothing.

1:02:25.791 --> 1:02:27.416
No money, nowhere to go.

1:02:28.458 --> 1:02:30.458
I knew Anna May from your dad's work.

1:02:32.041 --> 1:02:34.250
She and the other aunts took us in.

1:02:35.416 --> 1:02:37.291
The best years of my life.

1:02:37.375 --> 1:02:38.875
Me too.

1:02:42.708 --> 1:02:46.000
Fast-forward twelve years,
and I find out who shot your dad.

1:02:47.583 --> 1:02:48.875
The Russians?

1:02:49.708 --> 1:02:51.416
The Russians from the diner?

1:02:51.958 --> 1:02:55.375
Once I knew, I couldn't let him
walk around enjoying life…

1:02:57.208 --> 1:02:58.750
knowing what he did to us.

1:03:00.916 --> 1:03:04.416
But he was in bed with The Firm,
so there was a price to pay.

1:03:05.875 --> 1:03:08.250
Once I killed him,
there was a mark on my back.

1:03:10.666 --> 1:03:12.333
[soft emotional music]

1:03:15.291 --> 1:03:17.750
[voice breaks]
I couldn't take you with me.

1:03:20.208 --> 1:03:21.708
I couldn't risk your life.

1:03:25.208 --> 1:03:27.458
So I made Nathan promise to keep you safe.

1:03:31.750 --> 1:03:33.125
I guess that's over.

1:03:36.416 --> 1:03:39.916
There isn't a day that goes by
I don't regret pulling that trigger.

1:03:40.416 --> 1:03:42.625
But back then, I couldn't help myself.

1:03:47.208 --> 1:03:48.458
I'm sorry.

1:03:51.833 --> 1:03:53.625
[music fades out]

1:04:01.041 --> 1:04:03.333
Does the kid know about you and her dad?

1:04:03.416 --> 1:04:04.416
[Sam] No.

1:04:06.833 --> 1:04:08.166
But she's smart.

1:04:09.500 --> 1:04:10.666
She'll figure it out.

1:04:11.625 --> 1:04:13.125
What happens when she does?

1:04:21.625 --> 1:04:24.291
-[inaudible TV chatter]
-[soft emotional music]

1:04:30.416 --> 1:04:32.375
I think there's a bad man outside.

1:04:38.375 --> 1:04:39.708
We have to get out of here.

1:04:44.791 --> 1:04:47.583
-So, what's the plan?
-Can you press the lobby button?

1:04:47.666 --> 1:04:50.125
-What plan?
-Come on, you always have a plan.

1:04:50.208 --> 1:04:52.833
A secret escape route?
A warehouse filled with guns?

1:04:52.916 --> 1:04:53.958
I called us an Uber.

1:04:54.041 --> 1:04:55.500
-Are you kidding me?
-No.

1:04:55.583 --> 1:04:57.708
An Uber.
What the hell are you talking about?

1:04:57.791 --> 1:04:59.541
I know you. You make plans.

1:04:59.625 --> 1:05:01.791
And then you make plans
to make other plans.

1:05:01.875 --> 1:05:04.875
-You're frothing at the mouth.
-[rousing music]

1:05:04.958 --> 1:05:06.458
-It's unbecoming.
-[Sam scoffs]

1:05:12.833 --> 1:05:14.041
[elevator dings]

1:05:15.166 --> 1:05:17.083
[dramatic music]

1:05:25.208 --> 1:05:26.250
[whimpers]

1:05:27.333 --> 1:05:28.708
[screams] Get them!

1:05:28.791 --> 1:05:30.291
[men clamoring]

1:05:31.916 --> 1:05:34.083
[music intensifies]

1:05:34.166 --> 1:05:35.541
[mockingly] Don't feel bad.

1:05:36.041 --> 1:05:37.541
Could happen to anyone.

1:05:37.625 --> 1:05:39.333
My hand is still paralyzed.

1:05:39.416 --> 1:05:40.958
Yeah, course it is.

1:05:41.041 --> 1:05:42.875
-It is.
-I know.

1:05:42.958 --> 1:05:43.791
[elevator dings]

1:05:51.833 --> 1:05:53.625
[tense music]

1:05:54.500 --> 1:05:56.458
[Scarlet] Right. After you, ladies.

1:05:57.208 --> 1:05:59.041
[Scarlet] Come on. Hurry up.

1:05:59.708 --> 1:06:01.708
-[Sam] Where does it go?
-Fucking Narnia.

1:06:01.791 --> 1:06:02.791
Go. In.

1:06:03.291 --> 1:06:04.958
-In!
-[scoffs] Fine.

1:06:17.916 --> 1:06:20.958
-[Sam] No plan, huh?
-[Scarlet] Now is not the time.

1:06:21.916 --> 1:06:23.166
Out of my way.

1:06:27.500 --> 1:06:28.625
[echoing boom]

1:06:28.708 --> 1:06:30.916
-[Sam] Need help, Ma?
-No, thank you.

1:06:31.000 --> 1:06:32.208
I'm quite capable…

1:06:33.000 --> 1:06:36.000
of disposing of one…
[grunts]

1:06:36.083 --> 1:06:37.166
…idiotic grate.

1:06:47.166 --> 1:06:48.625
[hatch creaking]

1:06:51.458 --> 1:06:53.583
[suspenseful music]

1:07:03.416 --> 1:07:07.208
["Poupée de Cire, Poupée de Son"
by France Gall plays quietly]

1:07:07.291 --> 1:07:08.333
[banging]

1:07:08.416 --> 1:07:09.958
[clattering]

1:07:13.541 --> 1:07:17.000
[breathless] That freezer is a mess.
It's completely unacceptable.

1:07:20.166 --> 1:07:22.125
[dramatic music]

1:07:27.166 --> 1:07:29.333
-Come on.
-Are you kidding me?

1:07:29.875 --> 1:07:31.625
-We have to go.
-Go where?

1:07:31.708 --> 1:07:33.625
Obviously your plan was to end up here.

1:07:33.708 --> 1:07:35.708
-That was a long time ago.
-Mom…

1:07:36.458 --> 1:07:38.416
-I'm not going in there.
-Mom, listen.

1:07:38.500 --> 1:07:40.916
We need weapons and a car.
We need a safe house!

1:07:41.000 --> 1:07:43.291
I'm not sure they'd let me in!

1:07:43.375 --> 1:07:45.041
Only one way to find out.

1:07:46.458 --> 1:07:48.583
-[dramatic music]
-[church bells chiming]

1:07:54.750 --> 1:07:55.875
Hey.

1:08:11.041 --> 1:08:13.625
For the record,
I still think this is a shit idea.

1:08:17.041 --> 1:08:18.625
[dramatic music plays]

1:08:23.666 --> 1:08:25.541
[music fades out]

1:08:27.250 --> 1:08:28.458
Madeleine?

1:08:31.041 --> 1:08:32.833
-[Sam sighs]
-[gun cocking]

1:08:34.791 --> 1:08:37.791
[Anna May] Girls, I think I see a ghost.

1:08:42.708 --> 1:08:45.041
-Hi, Madeleine.
-Hi, Scarlet.

1:08:45.125 --> 1:08:46.291
[Scarlet] Florence.

1:08:48.750 --> 1:08:50.458
-Hi, Anna May.
-No.

1:08:51.125 --> 1:08:53.166
No, no. You don't get to talk.

1:08:54.291 --> 1:08:56.958
Because you're a ghost,
and ghosts can't talk.

1:08:57.458 --> 1:08:58.708
You know how I know that?

1:08:59.291 --> 1:09:00.666
Can we do this later?

1:09:00.750 --> 1:09:02.291
Because if ghosts could talk,

1:09:03.166 --> 1:09:05.875
they would say something
before disappearing.

1:09:05.958 --> 1:09:09.083
Or at least leave a note. But they can't.

1:09:09.166 --> 1:09:11.833
So, ipso facto, you're a ghost.

1:09:12.666 --> 1:09:14.250
-I'm sorry.
-[shouts] Fuck you.

1:09:14.333 --> 1:09:16.666
Language, Anna May.
There's a child present.

1:09:16.750 --> 1:09:18.041
Fine.

1:09:19.041 --> 1:09:21.583
-Fudge you.
-Fudge you.

1:09:21.666 --> 1:09:23.625
-Fudge you!
-[giggles]

1:09:25.791 --> 1:09:27.666
-[ominous music]
-[Emily giggles]

1:09:27.750 --> 1:09:30.916
And why is there a toddler
in our place of business?

1:09:32.708 --> 1:09:33.708
The short version?

1:09:34.500 --> 1:09:35.458
Please.

1:09:36.125 --> 1:09:39.000
Her father was killed
and she has nowhere else to go.

1:09:39.083 --> 1:09:40.708
I was downsized by The Firm,

1:09:40.791 --> 1:09:44.083
and they fed me to McAlester's
endless supply of thugs.

1:09:44.166 --> 1:09:45.791
And you decided to come here?

1:09:45.875 --> 1:09:47.708
Shall we return
at a more convenient time?

1:09:48.291 --> 1:09:49.541
Maybe you should.

1:09:49.625 --> 1:09:52.000
[Anna May] It seems like
whenever you come here,

1:09:52.083 --> 1:09:53.708
you bring a war with you.

1:09:56.000 --> 1:09:57.125
Bring your problems--

1:09:58.750 --> 1:10:00.125
We need to table this.

1:10:00.208 --> 1:10:02.000
[loud bang at door]

1:10:03.875 --> 1:10:05.041
Seconded.

1:10:05.583 --> 1:10:06.750
Let's go down.

1:10:11.708 --> 1:10:13.625
[multiple phones ringing]

1:10:15.208 --> 1:10:18.333
[phones ringing]

1:10:19.333 --> 1:10:20.916
[suspenseful music]

1:10:22.666 --> 1:10:24.000
[loud, resonant bang]

1:10:24.916 --> 1:10:26.291
Go and take Emily.

1:10:26.791 --> 1:10:28.291
I'll buy us some time.

1:10:30.500 --> 1:10:33.041
-I think I should stay.
-[banging]

1:10:35.333 --> 1:10:36.458
No.

1:10:37.041 --> 1:10:38.541
I screwed this up.

1:10:39.041 --> 1:10:41.333
-I'll clean up my own mess.
-[banging]

1:10:42.041 --> 1:10:44.666
We'll meet at the diner
once I've finished them off.

1:10:45.583 --> 1:10:47.958
-Go.
-[banging at door]

1:10:48.041 --> 1:10:49.208
Please.

1:10:51.500 --> 1:10:52.541
[whispers] Come.

1:10:55.125 --> 1:10:57.708
Are you sure?
I could use the target practice.

1:10:57.791 --> 1:10:58.791
Mm-mm.

1:10:59.291 --> 1:11:00.541
Anna May was right.

1:11:01.916 --> 1:11:03.958
I shouldn't have dragged you into this.

1:11:05.833 --> 1:11:08.416
[dramatic music intensifies]

1:11:13.333 --> 1:11:15.750
-[Emily] I'm staying with you.
-[sighs]

1:11:16.250 --> 1:11:18.041
-No. No, you're not.
-[door bangs]

1:11:18.125 --> 1:11:20.875
You're going to the basement,
where it's safe.

1:11:20.958 --> 1:11:23.458
But you need me. I'm your apprentice.

1:11:23.541 --> 1:11:25.291
[whispers] Okay, listen, Emily.

1:11:25.375 --> 1:11:28.750
The bad men are coming.
I really need you to go with my mom.

1:11:28.833 --> 1:11:31.333
No! I want to stay with you.

1:11:31.416 --> 1:11:32.708
-You can't.
-But why?

1:11:32.791 --> 1:11:34.291
Because…

1:11:35.375 --> 1:11:36.416
[swallows hard]

1:11:38.791 --> 1:11:40.500
Because I killed your father.

1:11:42.250 --> 1:11:45.291
You're lying.
You just want to get rid of me.

1:11:46.000 --> 1:11:47.375
[soft emotional music]

1:11:47.875 --> 1:11:49.291
Your dad, he, um…

1:11:50.291 --> 1:11:52.500
He stole from some very bad people.

1:11:54.083 --> 1:11:55.166
And they hired me.

1:11:55.666 --> 1:11:57.041
[door bangs]

1:11:57.666 --> 1:11:58.875
And I shot him.

1:12:05.708 --> 1:12:07.291
[Emily sobs quietly]

1:12:10.500 --> 1:12:13.083
-[Emily sniffs]
-Come on. Let's go.

1:12:17.625 --> 1:12:18.708
[door bangs]

1:12:22.250 --> 1:12:23.500
I need weapons.

1:12:23.583 --> 1:12:25.250
Try the self-help section.

1:12:31.833 --> 1:12:33.041
[door bangs]

1:12:37.625 --> 1:12:39.541
[door bangs loudly]

1:12:43.875 --> 1:12:45.041
[cocks gun]

1:12:52.375 --> 1:12:54.583
[suspenseful music]

1:12:58.958 --> 1:13:01.541
-[Scarlet] I have to help her.
-You need my permission?

1:13:01.625 --> 1:13:04.333
-I can't bail on her again.
-Why? You're good at it.

1:13:04.416 --> 1:13:08.333
I'm sorry I couldn't give it up back then
and just stay here with you.

1:13:11.000 --> 1:13:12.583
[sighs]

1:13:17.916 --> 1:13:19.250
You're human.

1:13:20.041 --> 1:13:21.458
You screwed up.

1:13:21.541 --> 1:13:25.041
I can only imagine
how painful it was leaving her behind.

1:13:28.291 --> 1:13:29.791
[banging intensifies]

1:13:32.916 --> 1:13:34.291
[metal screeching]

1:13:38.083 --> 1:13:39.625
Leaving us all behind.

1:13:41.125 --> 1:13:43.291
But she grew up to be a fine woman.

1:13:47.750 --> 1:13:49.416
[door bangs]

1:13:51.333 --> 1:13:53.250
I never wanted this life for her.

1:14:00.541 --> 1:14:01.958
Maybe it was meant to be.

1:14:02.041 --> 1:14:04.958
Or maybe she wanted to be
just like her mother.

1:14:09.750 --> 1:14:10.958
[metallic click]

1:14:12.500 --> 1:14:14.500
[slow footsteps]

1:14:15.458 --> 1:14:16.583
I missed you.

1:14:27.250 --> 1:14:29.083
We kept these ladies for you.

1:14:33.583 --> 1:14:35.500
[dramatic sting]

1:14:35.583 --> 1:14:37.750
[Anna May] Just meet us at the diner.

1:14:37.833 --> 1:14:39.583
Come back in one piece, okay?

1:14:40.708 --> 1:14:42.083
Both of you.

1:14:42.791 --> 1:14:44.583
[tense music]

1:14:46.958 --> 1:14:48.041
[grunts]

1:14:48.875 --> 1:14:50.416
[rock music plays]

1:14:51.875 --> 1:14:52.750
[grunts]

1:15:12.541 --> 1:15:13.791
-[blows]
-[grunts]

1:15:14.583 --> 1:15:16.458
[both grunting]

1:15:21.625 --> 1:15:22.750
[metallic thud]

1:15:25.708 --> 1:15:27.750
[both strenuously grunting]

1:15:34.333 --> 1:15:35.833
[screams]

1:15:36.625 --> 1:15:37.791
[strained grunting]

1:15:41.833 --> 1:15:43.000
[grunts]

1:15:46.375 --> 1:15:47.666
[Sam grunts]

1:15:56.541 --> 1:15:57.791
Motherfucker!

1:16:06.666 --> 1:16:07.791
[gun clicks]

1:16:10.500 --> 1:16:11.416
[Sam screams]

1:16:13.333 --> 1:16:14.875
-[kicking]
-[grunting]

1:16:19.208 --> 1:16:21.000
[intense musical build-up]

1:16:25.000 --> 1:16:26.500
[gunshots]

1:16:33.041 --> 1:16:34.291
[music fades]

1:16:37.333 --> 1:16:38.583
[soft music]

1:16:40.000 --> 1:16:41.333
[Sam grunts]

1:16:43.166 --> 1:16:44.708
Is anything broken?

1:16:44.791 --> 1:16:46.333
-Are you bleeding?
-I'm fine.

1:16:46.416 --> 1:16:47.875
Bleeding on the inside?

1:16:49.625 --> 1:16:51.166
The rest of them are coming.

1:16:51.250 --> 1:16:53.208
Would it kill you to say thank you?

1:16:54.333 --> 1:16:56.625
You can still go, Ma. I'll cover you.

1:16:57.291 --> 1:16:59.541
-And miss all the fun?
-[music fades out]

1:17:05.625 --> 1:17:07.208
Women Who Run with the Wolves.

1:17:09.250 --> 1:17:11.541
-Awakening the Giant Within.
-[grunts] Ammo?

1:17:11.625 --> 1:17:13.583
How to Win Friends and Influence People.

1:17:14.791 --> 1:17:16.166
[quiet creaking]

1:17:20.041 --> 1:17:22.458
[door shuts in far distance]

1:17:28.458 --> 1:17:29.666
[grunts]

1:17:32.166 --> 1:17:34.625
You should've stayed away
from this line of work.

1:17:34.708 --> 1:17:36.291
Are you kidding, Ma?

1:17:37.458 --> 1:17:38.500
You left.

1:17:39.041 --> 1:17:41.791
Killing people was the only thing
I knew how to do.

1:17:42.333 --> 1:17:45.833
Okay, maybe it wasn't the best environment
to raise a child in.

1:17:45.916 --> 1:17:47.375
[sarcastic] You think?

1:17:48.833 --> 1:17:50.416
It made you who you are.

1:17:50.500 --> 1:17:52.250
At least we can agree on that.

1:17:55.416 --> 1:17:57.208
[soft emotional music]

1:18:05.500 --> 1:18:08.708
And you are a strong, smart,
incredibly impressive young woman.

1:18:10.916 --> 1:18:14.291
There's not a single person on earth
I'd rather kill people with.

1:18:15.916 --> 1:18:17.083
Thanks, Ma.

1:18:18.166 --> 1:18:21.750
[Madeleine] You're so strong!
You can't be 8 and three quarters.

1:18:21.833 --> 1:18:22.875
[Emily] I am.

1:18:22.958 --> 1:18:25.625
[Madeleine] You sure you're not
28 and three quarters?

1:18:26.208 --> 1:18:27.875
[van door slides shut]

1:18:29.750 --> 1:18:31.333
[eerie music]

1:18:33.916 --> 1:18:36.416
Anna May, Madeleine. Come and see this.

1:18:37.958 --> 1:18:40.416
[suspenseful music]

1:18:45.625 --> 1:18:46.833
[whispers] Oh.

1:18:47.541 --> 1:18:49.083
We're not leaving.

1:18:49.583 --> 1:18:52.625
Scarlet's still a librarian,
no matter if she's an asshole.

1:18:52.708 --> 1:18:54.458
-Language.
-Right.

1:18:55.000 --> 1:18:57.416
-So these…
-Jerks.

1:18:57.500 --> 1:18:59.416
…jerks up there

1:19:00.166 --> 1:19:02.708
just made the biggest mistake
of their lives.

1:19:02.791 --> 1:19:06.791
[Anna May] They stepped into our library
and threatened our own flesh and blood.

1:19:06.875 --> 1:19:08.708
They're not gonna push us around.

1:19:08.791 --> 1:19:12.500
They're not gonna scare us off.
This ends now.

1:19:12.583 --> 1:19:15.541
Madeleine, finish getting the van ready.

1:19:15.625 --> 1:19:19.666
Florence, you and I are going up there
to thin the herd.

1:19:20.291 --> 1:19:24.458
We're gonna bring the sky down
on their mother-fudging heads.

1:19:25.000 --> 1:19:26.000
All in favor?

1:19:26.083 --> 1:19:28.166
-Aye.
-Aye.

1:19:29.500 --> 1:19:30.458
Aye.

1:19:30.541 --> 1:19:31.875
[music intensifies]

1:19:33.291 --> 1:19:34.666
Motion carried.

1:19:38.625 --> 1:19:40.416
[soft dreamy music plays]

1:19:40.500 --> 1:19:41.875
[inaudible]

1:20:01.416 --> 1:20:03.166
[dreamy music fades out]

