1:31:22.000 --> 1:31:23.791
[quietly] I couldn't save her.

1:31:24.333 --> 1:31:26.250
[whispers] It's okay.

1:31:26.333 --> 1:31:28.000
We'll get her back.

1:31:31.208 --> 1:31:33.250
[soft emotional music]

1:31:42.000 --> 1:31:43.291
It was nice…

1:31:44.000 --> 1:31:46.375
having a kid in the library again.

1:31:49.375 --> 1:31:50.500
Huh?

1:32:11.916 --> 1:32:13.708
[emotional music]

1:32:35.958 --> 1:32:38.791
[Anna May]
"There is little joy in life for me"

1:32:39.916 --> 1:32:42.875
"And little terror in the grave"

1:32:42.958 --> 1:32:46.500
"I've lived the parting hour to see"

1:32:46.583 --> 1:32:50.208
"Of one I would have died to save"

1:33:10.791 --> 1:33:12.625
[cheerful ringtone plays]

1:33:14.916 --> 1:33:18.750
[nephew] Well, that was exciting.
Been a long time since I killed someone.

1:33:19.375 --> 1:33:20.833
Let me talk to Emily.

1:33:21.750 --> 1:33:23.458
[nephew] It's a real tragedy

1:33:23.541 --> 1:33:26.833
what happens to poor orphans
in our line of work, you know?

1:33:27.625 --> 1:33:29.000
It's really quite sad.

1:33:31.875 --> 1:33:33.083
What do you want?

1:33:33.958 --> 1:33:36.083
[nephew] My uncle insists on meeting you.

1:33:36.166 --> 1:33:38.291
He says, skinning you alive will let him

1:33:38.375 --> 1:33:40.875
work through his, uh, grief.

1:33:41.958 --> 1:33:43.958
That's not too much to ask, is it?

1:33:44.041 --> 1:33:45.458
If I come to you,

1:33:46.208 --> 1:33:47.583
Emily goes free.

1:33:48.625 --> 1:33:50.458
And everyone else is off the table.

1:33:55.083 --> 1:33:56.791
[nephew] Okay, we have a deal.

1:33:57.458 --> 1:33:58.416
The diner.

1:33:59.166 --> 1:34:00.416
[nephew] Can't wait.

1:34:02.125 --> 1:34:03.083
We gotta go.

1:34:03.875 --> 1:34:06.666
You can't just hand yourself over
to those animals.

1:34:06.750 --> 1:34:08.916
They can't bring guns into the diner.

1:34:09.708 --> 1:34:12.666
-It's Emily's best chance.
-It's a suicide mission.

1:34:12.750 --> 1:34:14.833
Well, someone else got a plan? Hmm?

1:34:18.083 --> 1:34:20.250
I, uh… I don't right now, no.

1:34:22.583 --> 1:34:24.166
[whispers] But it's you, Mom.

1:34:26.833 --> 1:34:28.500
[whispers] You always have a plan.

1:34:29.458 --> 1:34:30.541
Sorry.

1:34:36.250 --> 1:34:38.000
Then I guess this is goodbye.

1:34:41.791 --> 1:34:43.125
[Sam sighs]

1:34:47.750 --> 1:34:49.666
-[soft music]
-[birdsong]

1:34:52.583 --> 1:34:54.625
[trees creak quietly]

1:35:04.958 --> 1:35:06.916
[slow tense music plays]

1:35:14.291 --> 1:35:15.916
They're waiting for you, honey.

1:35:16.875 --> 1:35:18.166
[Sam] Thanks, Rose.

1:35:33.375 --> 1:35:35.083
[eerie music]

1:35:38.833 --> 1:35:40.333
Did they hurt you?

1:35:45.541 --> 1:35:47.375
It's been a long day.

1:35:48.708 --> 1:35:50.291
It's gonna be over soon, okay?

1:35:52.416 --> 1:35:53.500
[whispers] Okay.

1:36:04.958 --> 1:36:06.666
You're a special kid, Emily.

1:36:08.750 --> 1:36:11.125
I wish I had more time to get to know you.

1:36:15.791 --> 1:36:17.333
[ominous music plays]

1:36:25.000 --> 1:36:26.625
[music fades]

1:36:27.500 --> 1:36:28.750
I'm Jim.

1:36:29.916 --> 1:36:31.166
Samantha.

1:36:33.958 --> 1:36:35.250
You know, Samantha…

1:36:36.458 --> 1:36:39.750
I've always considered myself a feminist.

1:36:41.416 --> 1:36:45.125
When my first daughter was born,
I was over the moon.

1:36:46.375 --> 1:36:48.291
Painted half the house pink.

1:36:49.041 --> 1:36:52.458
It was all unicorns and lollipops.

1:36:54.625 --> 1:36:56.708
And my second daughter was born.

1:36:58.041 --> 1:37:00.208
And the third and the fourth.

1:37:02.333 --> 1:37:03.500
Girls…

1:37:05.250 --> 1:37:08.083
always whispering at the dining table.

1:37:10.041 --> 1:37:12.500
Always giggling in dark corners.

1:37:15.166 --> 1:37:16.791
I love my girls.

1:37:18.041 --> 1:37:19.791
But I don't understand them.

1:37:23.333 --> 1:37:24.916
Then my son was born.

1:37:26.791 --> 1:37:28.083
It was different.

1:37:28.833 --> 1:37:29.833
Simple.

1:37:32.666 --> 1:37:34.250
We understood each other.

1:37:36.083 --> 1:37:37.875
And I wasn't alone any more.

1:37:45.541 --> 1:37:46.833
I know…

1:37:49.291 --> 1:37:51.625
it was just a job to you, and he was…

1:37:52.541 --> 1:37:54.875
in the wrong place at the wrong time.

1:37:55.416 --> 1:37:57.166
[soft music]

1:37:57.250 --> 1:37:58.625
None of that matters,

1:37:59.791 --> 1:38:02.625
